node.text:
New England Lobster Roll or Top Cut Hot Dog Bun? Follow the recipe👇🏻
- In the bowl of a stand mixer, combine 2 1/2 cups of all purpose flour, 1/4 cup of dry milk powder, 1/4 cup of potato flakes, 2 tablespoons of granulated sugar, 1 1/2 teaspoons of salt, and 2 1/4 tablespoons of instant yeast
- Mix in 1 1/4 cup of warm water and run the mixer with the dough hook for about 2 minutes or until the dough is smooth,then add 2 tablespoons of softened butter
- - When the dough comes together and is smooth, transfer it to a greased bowl, and cover it for roughly 2 hours
- When the dough has risen, punch it down and equally separate it into 10 equal balls
- Roll it into a smooth ball for a few minutes and then press it into a tube shape the same size of the hot dog tray
- These trays are easily found on amazon, cover it and let it rest for 45 minutes
- After the 45 minutes, cover the buns in a beaten egg wash and bake it at 375 degrees F for 20 minutes
- Let the buns cool,. then cut them along the middle of the top for the top cut!

Ketchup Powder aka Ketchup Seasoning. Follow the recipe👇🏻
- Place a silpat mat on a baking tray
- Squirt on 1/4 cup of ketchup and spread it evenly
- Place it in a 200 degree F oven for 7 hours
- Take it out and let it cool, then separate the ketchup from the tray and place it in a spice grinder
- Grind it until a fine powder forms
- Use this seasoning on fries, chips, or even popcorn

node.text:
Cheese Stuffed Mashed Potato Doughnut. Follow the recipe👇🏻
- Mash together 2 cups of yukon gold potatoes with 2 tablespoons of butter, 1 tablespoon of garlic powder, 1/4 cup of chopped parsley and salt and pepper
- Using a cake doughnut pan, fill each slot with an equal amount of the potato mixture
- Pull apart a piece of string cheese to get 4 pieces
- Press two pieces of the cheese into each doughnut and place them in the freezer for 30 minutes
- In a bowl, combine 2 cups of panko bread crumbs, with 1 cup of potato flake, 1 tablespoon of smoked paprika and garlic powder powder, and a pinch of salt and pepper
- In another bowl whisk together 4 eggs
- When the mashed potato doughnuts are solid, remove them from the slot using a toothpick and coat them in the egg wash, then into the bread crumb mixture, and repeat for a double dredge
- Fry them, at 375 degrees F for 3 minutes or air fry them at 400 degrees F for 10 minutes
- These are great as is,but even better dipped in gravy

Beef Salami Breakfast Sandwich. Follow the recipe👇🏻
- Pan fry 4 slices of beef salami on medium high heat
- Make a small cut into each piece of salami so it doesn't curl when cooking
- Place a slice of American cheese on top of one piece, and add another piece of salami on top. Set them aside
- Spread some mayonnaise on an English muffin and pan toast them for a few minutes just until they are lightly toasted and golden brown
- Add some butter to a medium pan, and fry some eggs to your liking (about 3-4 minutes for sunny side up)
- Place the salami on one half of the English muffin, followed by the egg on top
- #neverskipeggday and enjoy!

Blooming Apple Pie. Follow the recipe👇🏻
- In a bowl, combine 2 cups of buttermilk with 2 eggs
- In another bowl, combine 2 cups of all purpose flour with 2 tablespoons of cinnamon and nutmeg and a pinch of salt
- Using an apple cutter and two spatulas to prevent the apple from cutting all the way through, slice a granny smith apple or whatever apple of your choice
- Use a fork or another apple coring tool to remove the inside core trying to keep the apple from separating
- Submerge the apple in the buttermilk mixture making sure to fully coat it
- Bring it to the seasoned flour and coat it thoroughly
- Repeat this for a double dredge
- Fry the apple at 350 degrees F for 5 minutes
- In the meantime, combine 1 cup of sugar with 2 tablespoons of cinnamon
- When the apple is done frying, toss it in the bowl of cinnamon sugar and thoroughly coat it
- These are great as is, but even better if you dip them in caramel

Fried Chicken Hot Dog with a Tangy Sauce. Follow the recipe👇🏻
- Add 2 cups of butter milk and 1/2 cup of pickle juice to a bowl
- Submerge a few chicken tenders and let marinate for at least 30 minutes
- For the buns I used golden hot dog buns and cut them on the top like a New England lobster roll
- Brush them with some egg wash to make them shiny and crispy, and bake for 5 minutes at 450 degrees F
- In the meantime, make the sauce by combining 1 cup of mayonnaise, with 1/4 cup of ketchup, 2 tablespoons of Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder and black pepper
- For the dry dredge for the chicken, combine 1 cup of all purpose flour,. 2 tablespoons of paprika, garlic powder, and salt in a bowl 
- Submerge the marinated chicken in the flour mixture and press it into the chicken for a crunchy fry, repeat that for a double dredge
- Fry the chicken at 375 degrees F for 5 minutes
- Take the chicken out and immediately season with salt
- To make the sandwiches, add some of the sauce to the bottom of the fried chicken tender, some bread and butter pickles on the side and some more sauce on top!

5 Ingredient Oreo Cake Doughnuts. Follow the recipe👇🏻
- Crush about 20 Oreos in a food processor
- In the bowl of a stand mixer, combine 2 cups of self rising flour with 1 cup of crushed Oreos and 1 cup of greek yogurt
- When the dough pulls together, turn it out on a floured surface for a few minutes just until the dough is smooth
- Roll out the dough until its about 2 inches thick, and then use a large cookie cutter to make teh doughnut shape, and a smaller cookie cutter to cut out the inside
- reserve the small insides for doughnut ho9les
- Place the doughnuts on a parchment paper lined baking tray and let rest for 5 minutes
- Bake the doughnuts at 400 degrees F for 10 minutes, flipping halfway through
- In the meantime, combine 2 cups of powdered sugar with 1/4 cup of corn syrup
- Dip the cooled doughnuts in the glaze letting any excess glaze drip off and then place them on a wire rack
- Garnish with some additional crushed Oreos

Buffalo Chicken Jalapeño Popper Bites. Follow the recipe👇🏻
- Season 1/2 pound of chicken breasts with salt and onion powder
- Fry them on medium high for 3 minutes a side and transfer the chicken toa food processor
- Pulse the chicken a few times to break it up, then add 1/2 cup of cooked bacon bits, 1 cup of room temperature cream cheese, 1 cup of sharp shredded cheddar, 1 tablespoon of onion powder, garlic powder, and paprika, and a pinch of salt.
- Run the food processor and then add 1/4 cup of your favorite hot sauce
- Transfer the mixture to a piping bag or p[lastic freezer bag
- Cut the top off a large jalapeño and using a fork, scoop out the seeds and stems from the inside
- Fill the jalapeno up with the chicken and cheese mixture and then slice them into 1 inch pieces
- Put them in the freezer for about 10 minutes
- In a bowl combine 5 eggs with 1/2 cup of hot sauce and in another bowl combine 2 cups of all purpose flour with 1/4 cup of paprika and garlic powder and ina 3rd bowl 2 cups of bread crumbs
- Coat the jalapeño piece in the flour, the in the egg wash, then in the bread crumbs, then back in the egg wash and breadcrumbs for a double dredge
- Fry the jalapeños at 375 degrees F for 3-4 minutes or airfryer at 425 for 10 minutes

Big Mac Inspired Hot Dog aka a McGlizzy. Follow the recipe👇🏻
- Start off by making the sesame seed buns but using top cut (New England) buns
- Coat the with a beaten egg wash and then sprinkle on some sesame seeds
- Bake the buns at 450 degrees F for 5 minutes
- For the big mac sauce, combine 1/2 cup of mayonnaise, 1/4 cup of ketchup and mustard, 1 tablespoon of garlic and onion powder, 1 tablespoon of sweet relish and white vinegar, and season with salt and pepper
- Fry a few all beef hot dogs to your liking and set them aside
- Assemble the hot dogs by adding some sauce on the inside followed by a bit of small diced onions
- On top of the onions add some shredded iceberg lettuce followed by a couple slices of American cheese
- Add a few slices of mini dill pickles between the bun and the cheese. The cheese will help the pickles stay in place
- Add the hot dog on top of the cheese followed by some more diced onions and some more Big Mac sauce
